		<summary>
			<para>Initializes a new instance of the <see cref="System.ComponentModel.ListChangedEventArgs"/> class, with the
 way the list changed and a <see cref="System.ComponentModel.PropertyDescriptor"/> .</para>
		</summary>
		<param name="listChangedType">One of the <see cref="System.ComponentModel.ListChangedType"/> values.</param>
		<param name=" propDesc">A <see cref="System.ComponentModel.PropertyDescriptor"/> that was added, removed, or changed.</param>
		<remarks>
			<para> This constructor can be used only if the schema of the object has
 changed.</para>
			<para>The <paramref name="listChangedType"/> parameter should be <see cref="System.ComponentModel.ListChangedType.PropertyDescriptorAdded" qualify="true"/>, <see cref="System.ComponentModel.ListChangedType.PropertyDescriptorChanged" qualify="true"/>, or <see cref="System.ComponentModel.ListChangedType.PropertyDescriptorDeleted" qualify="true"/>.</para>
		</remarks>
		<seealso cref="System.ComponentModel.ListChangedEventArgs.ListChangedType"/>
	</doc>
	<doc for="ListChangedEventArgs">
		<summary>
			<para>Provides data for the <see cref="System.ComponentModel.IBindingList.ListChanged"/> event.</para>
		</summary>
		<remarks>
			<para>A <see cref="System.ComponentModel.IBindingList.ListChanged"/> event is
   raised when the data in an <see cref="System.ComponentModel.IBindingList"/>
   changes.</para>
			<para>When a <see cref="System.ComponentModel.IBindingList.ListChanged"/> event is fired, 
a single index for deletion needs to be specified. You can set the
<paramref name="newIndex"/> of <see cref="M:System.ComponentModel.ListChangedEventArgs.#ctor"/> to the index you 
are deleting. If there is only one index in the <see cref="System.ComponentModel.IBindingList"/>
, <paramref name="oldIndex"/> should be set to -1. </para>
		</remarks>
		<example>
			<para>For an example on using this class, see <see topic="cpconworkingwithdataviewevents"/>.</para>
		</example>
	</doc>
